Henley Group Inc's M.W. Kellogg Co unitsaid it was selected by &lt;Chinese Petroleum Corp> to design,engineer and build a ethylene plant at ChinesePetroleum's Kaohsiung refinery in Taiwan.    Terms of the contract were not disclosed, but Kellogg saidthe total cost of the plant will be 300 mln dlrs.    Kellogg said engineering of the plant, which will have acapacity of 400,000 tonnes a year, is already underway andconstruction will begin in 1988.    The plant will go into operation in 1990, Kellogg said. Reuter&#3;